[4] Mexico (Mexico City)
Date: Mon 4 May 2020
Source: The Yucatan Times [abridged, edited]
https://www.theyucatantimes.com/2020/05/measles-increases-number-of-infections-to-163-cases-in-cdmx/


The latest report issued by the Health Department on [Fri 1 May 2020], states that Mexico City continues to be the area with the most cases of measles. Specifically, the Municipality of Gustavo A Madero is responsible for 42.9% of the cases. The epidemiological report on measles revealed that in the State of Mexico there are about 30 cases, and the most affected area is the municipality of Ecatepec, while in the state of Campeche 2 cases have already been reported, which are being closely monitored.

However, of the total number of people infected with measles, only 19% said they have a history of vaccination and the vast majority said they do not have it, in addition the oldest person who has contracted the disease is an adult over 67 years, while the youngest is a 3 month old baby.

Following up on this disease is of utmost importance since according to WHO, measles is one of the main causes of death among children, although in Mexico no deaths have been registered yet, the virus should not be downplayed.

